.TH "snd_hdac_codec_write" 9 "snd_hdac_codec_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_codec_write \- send a single command without waiting for response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hdac_codec_write
.BI "(struct hdac_device *hdac "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "unsigned int verb "  ","
.BI "unsigned int parm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdac" 12
the HDAC device
.IP "nid" 12
NID to send the command
.IP "flags" 12
optional bit flags
.IP "verb" 12
the verb to send
.IP "parm" 12
the parameter for the verb
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a single command without waiting for response.

Returns 0 if successful, or a negative error code.
